"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-12-Behind-Breaking-s-Olympic-debut-China-s-thriving-street-dance-scene-1vZ6MWAOVkk-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Copied  Editor's Note: CGTN is launching EconSports Beat, a new series that focuses on the rise of emerging Olympic sports like skateboarding, surfing, and sport climbing. Join us as we explore the exciting world of these popular Olympic events, uncovering innovative business models and highlighting the numerous opportunities they offer to sports enthusiasts.  Breakdancing, the first dance sport in the Olympics, has made its historic Olympic debut at the 2024 Paris Games. Once a niche subculture, street dance has grown into a vibrant industry in China. Our reporter, Sun Shangyi, explores the thriving street dance scene that's emerging in dance studios around the country.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"